AGI - The City of Turbigo of the Metropolitan City of Milan, led by a coalition of centre-rights, must respond to the local Muslim community "within the hours 14 of the day 5 April 2024 to the request of granting a place indoors or outdoors to celebrate the feast of end Ramadan and, in the event of a negative response, will take care to indicate any spaces that would be suitable for use and the reasons of their unavailableness". This is what we read in a decision of the Tar of Lombardy visioned by the AGI coming, explains lawyer Luca Bauccio, legal of the religious association 'Moschea Essa'&nbsp; together with his colleague Aldo Russo, "after that in three months the Municipality did not respond to three requests of the Muslim community to obtain a space to celebrate the end of Ramadan, the Aid El Fitr".
&nbsp;
The appeal had been presented precisely 'against' the silence held by the Municipality on the application dated 26 February 2024 of the association "so that the Municipality provides to make available on 9 and 10 April 2024, in the hourly period between 7 and 11, a covered or uncovered space, in which to celebrate the Muslim feast". In the decree the president of the fifth section of the Tar, Daniele Dongiovanni, writes that "to the request advanced from the association in the within of the recourse in matter of silence can be adequate protection, honoring the Commune to conquer celermente the investigation regarding the instance and provide a written answer within the term of the hours 14 of 5 April 2024". The same municipal statute, is remembered by the judge, previews that to every instance the Municipality should provide "within 30 days from the date of protocol, term now expired". The Municipality of Turbigo, led by the mayor of Fratelli d'Italia Fabrizio Allevi, had not been in judgement.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;"We once again witness the denial of a fundamental right recognized by the Constitution to all religious minorities: the right to prayer and religious identity - comments to AGI Bauccio -. The Tar has correctly remembered that the administration has the duty to guarantee the spaces of encounter and prayer and a possible denial must always be motivated. We will continue until the Muslim community of Turbigo is guaranteed the full enjoyment of the fundamental rights of the person. A free and democratic society does not ignore minorities and care and attention to their legitimate demands." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp; In the appeal submitted to the Tar against the Municipality of Turbigo, the lawyers of the Muslim cultural association 'Essa' write that, if a space should not be recognized to celebrate the end of Ramadan, "we will be forced to act in every competent place for the complete refreshment of damages".
&nbsp;
"The association - it is written in the instance read by the AGI - is devoid of its own place of worship. Waiting to be able to dispose, especially on the occasion of the main celebrations and festivities, it has the need for an adequate and dignified place that allows the serene exercise of that fundamental freedom that is religious freedom, as well as that of worship guaranteed by article 19 of the Constitution as an inviolable right, to be understood not as indifference of the State in the face of religious experience, but as protection of pluralism, in support of the maximum expansion of freedom of all".
&nbsp;
The association has sent three requests via Pec to the Municipality to have indication of a place where to celebrate the end of Ramadan dated 26 February and 22 and 25 March, "only all fallen into the void".
&nbsp;
"The Commune - the Bauccio and Russo lawyers say - has failed to its duty linked to constitutional freedoms and guarantees not having provided adequate and dignified space to allow the Muslim community to celebrate the end of Ramadan."

