&nbsp;
"We are a multicultural, multilingual community, including by statute and mission, a friend of diversity and committed to building the recognition of the other as a precondition for a peaceful coexistence between peoples and cultures," is the explanation of the choice they give from the athenean.
&nbsp;
"At this terrible time, a moment in which all the West becomes an accomplice to the endless massacre of Gaza, it is important - they continue - to give a precise sign of friendship and sharing with people who - among us, in Siena, in Italy and in the world - recognize themselves in Islamic culture". Also confirmed the will to suspend the teaching for the Jewish feast of Kippur> "to emphasize - it is explained - our closeness to the Jewish people in the anniversary of the massacre of October 7". &nbsp;

