AGI - Two 14 and 15-year-old boys died in Nuoro for the collapse of the loft of an abandoned building.&nbsp; The transfer of the roof took place in Via Pasquale Dessanay. Firefighters arrived at 20:00. The operating station of the 118 of Sassari sent on the place a medicalized ambulance of Nuoro and a basic means of Oliena, but for the two teenagers there was nothing to do. I also intervened the carabinieri.&nbsp; The two victims were called Patrick Zola and Ethan Romano.
&nbsp;
The tragedy took place in Badu and Carros. The boys were probably playing in the abandoned building, when two perimeter walls collapsed on the first floor and one loft. The Regional Direction for Sardinia of the Fire Brigade has placed two SAPR units on the spot for a reconnaissance flight to capture images and videos that can be useful for the coordinated investigations of the Proxy, which in the meantime placed the site under seizure.&nbsp;
<div </div
<h2> The draft of the mayor
"There are no words, if not a deep pain, when two young lives are broken suddenly," says the mayor of Nuoro, Andrea Soddu. "In this painful circumstance, I express the most felt condolences, on my behalf and the entire City of Nuoro, to the families of Patrick and Ethan so hard hit by this immense tragedy. That solidarity and support can soothe, even if only in part, the suffering of a huge loss, like that of two boys who had all their lives ahead. A sincere thanks to the rescue teams of firefighters, 118 and law enforcement forces for the promptness and efficiency demonstrated in their intervention."
&nbsp;

